{"questionId":"29618851","questionHtml":"<p>On the following axes, sketch the graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mrow><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>≤</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>6</mn></math>.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/fee4b86e073eb51a5ea02f98a58efe83baa799be.png\" width=\"683\" height=\"394\"></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><img src=\"__IMG__/81d7ee8d2aaafee01fbbb890022827568b2dae3f.png\" width=\"573\" height=\"416\"></p>\n<p>reflection of all negative sections in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-axis&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p>approximately correct graph with sharp points (cusps) at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-intercepts&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <strong><em>A1</em></strong> only if the heights of the maximum in the middle are lower than the heights of the maximum at the ends.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"29618851","referenceCode":"24M.1.AHL.TZ1.9a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"On the following axes, sketch the graph of y=fx for -6≤x≤6.","paper":"1","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.11—Definite integrals, areas under curve onto x-axis and areas between curves","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.3—Graphing","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.14—Odd and even functions, self-inverse, inverse and domain restriction","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.16—Graphing modulus equations and inequalities"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}